==English==

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|en|gussie up}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|gussies up|gussying up|gussied up}}

# {{lb|en|informal}} To [[don]] fancy clothing; to [[dress up]] particularly in flattering or specially altered garments.
#: ''You bet she'll '''gussy up''' for the party.''
# {{lb|en|informal}} To make [[fancy]] or [[attractive]], as by [[artificial]] or [[contrived]] means.
#: ''You can have plain green beans, or '''gussie''' them '''up''' with a bit of cheese and onion.''
#: {{syn|en|spruce up}}

